routeFacts.name: Midland Mainline
routeFacts.description: Midland Main Line: Leicester - Nottingham and Derby is a DLC route for Train Sim World 3, developed by Skyhook Games. It depicts the central section of the Midlands Main Line, covering the section from Leicester to Derby, plus the branch from East Midlands Parkway to Nottingham. Also featured is Ratcliffe Power Station, Eastcroft Depot and Litchurch Lane Works.
routeInfo: The route is set in 2019, towards the end of East Midlands Trains before the East Midlands franchise was transferred to Abellio to form East Midlands Railway operator. It features the BR Class 43 HST for high-speed intercity services, and the BR Class 158 for regional and commuter services. This is the first modern diesel route for the UK since Great Western Express, which was also the BR Class 43 HST's last appearance, until now.
